%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc1030v3p1r8o%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc1030v3p1r8o.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc1030v3p1r8o.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Southwest%20Monsoon%20Likely%20To%20Reach%20Kerala%20Around%20May%2031%3A%20Weather%20Office%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ESouthwest%20Monsoon%20is%20likely%20to%20arrive%20over%20Kerala%20around%20May%2031%2C%20setting%20the%20stage%20for%20the%20four-month%20rainfall%20season%20crucial%20for%20India's%20farm-based%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20year%2C%20the%20Southwest%20Monsoon%20is%20likely%20to%20set%20over%20Kerala%20on%20May%2031%20with%20a%20model%20error%20of%20four%20days%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20India%20Meteorological%20Department%20said%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20early%3B%20it's%20close%20to%20the%20normal%20date%2C%26quot%3B%20IMD%20Director%20General%20Mrutyunjay%20Mohapatra%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20date%20of%20monsoon%20onset%20over%20Kerala%20has%20varied%20widely%20over%20the%20last%20150%20years%2C%20the%20earliest%20being%20May%2011%2C%201918%2C%20and%20the%20most%20delayed%20being%20June%2018%2C%201972%2C%20according%20to%20IMD%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20rain-bearing%20system%20arrived%20in%20the%20southern%20state%20on%20June%208%20last%20year%2C%20May%2029%20in%202022%2C%20June%203%20in%202021%20and%20June%201%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20month%2C%20the%20IMD%20had%20forecast%20above-normal%20rain%20in%20the%20monsoon%20season%20in%20India%20with%20favourable%20La%20Nina%20conditions%20expected%20to%20set%20in%20by%20August-September.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParts%20of%20the%20country%20battled%20brutal%20heat%20in%20April%2C%20with%20maximum%20temperatures%20shattering%20records%20in%20several%20states%20and%20severely%20impacting%20health%20and%20livelihoods.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20crippling%20heat%20is%20straining%20power%20grids%20and%20drying%20up%20water%20bodies%20triggering%20drought-like%20conditions%20in%20parts%20of%20the%20country.%20A%20prediction%20of%20above-normal%20monsoonal%20rainfall%2C%20therefore%2C%20comes%20as%20a%20huge%20relief%20to%20the%20fast-developing%20South%20Asian%20nation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20monsoon%20is%20critical%20for%20India's%20agricultural%20landscape%2C%20with%2052%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20net%20cultivated%20area%20relying%20on%20it.%20It%20is%20also%20crucial%20for%20replenishing%20reservoirs%20critical%20for%20drinking%20water%2C%20apart%20from%20power%20generation%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJune%20and%20July%20are%20considered%20the%20most%20important%20monsoon%20months%20for%20agriculture%20because%20most%20of%20the%20sowing%20for%20the%20Kharif%20crop%20takes%20place%20during%20this%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEl%20Nino%20conditions%20are%20prevailing%20at%20present%2C%20and%20La%20Nina%20may%20set%20in%20by%20August-September%2C%20scientists%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEl%20Nino%20-%20the%20periodic%20warming%20of%20surface%20waters%20in%20the%20central%20Pacific%20Ocean%20-%20is%20associated%20with%20weaker%20monsoon%20winds%20and%20drier%20conditions%20in%20India.%20La%20Nina%20-%20the%20antithesis%20of%20El%20Nino-%20leads%20to%20plentiful%20rainfall%20during%20the%20monsoon%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IMD%20is%20also%20anticipating%20the%20development%20of%20a%20positive%20Indian%20Ocean%20Dipole%20(IOD)%20or%20cooler-than-normal%20Indian%20Ocean%20in%20the%20east%20compared%20to%20the%20west%2C%20which%20helps%20bring%20rain%20to%20several%20states%20in%20southern%20India.%20The%20IOD%20is%20currently%20'neutral'%20and%20is%20expected%20to%20turn%20positive%20by%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20factor%20is%20below-normal%20snow%20cover%20in%20the%20northern%20hemisphere%20and%20Eurasia.%20Historically%2C%20there%20has%20been%20an%20%